Priyanka
Team PluginHive

Hi,&nbsp; 





A password reset link has been sent to support@pluginhive.com&nbsp; 





Once reset, you can access the admin here - 
https://store-17gicadb8v.mybigcommerce.com/manage 









Regards, 

Kennedy Wild

Hello Kennedy Wild,
&nbsp;
Thank you for the access.
&nbsp;
We will also require access to the Order Notification settings to review the settings used on your store.
&nbsp;
Additionally, I would like to clarify that the Order Completion emails are sent by BigCommerce and not the app. The app only adds the tracking number to the BigCommerce Order which is added in the email by BigCommerce.
&nbsp;
So, it may not be possible to show the ParcelForce service name in the email from the app.
&nbsp;
For your second case, the order notes are already printed on the labels by the app. Attached screenshots of order 93698 where the order note is printed on the label.
&nbsp;
Please note that there is a character limit of 25 characters to print the information on the label.
&nbsp;
Let us know if you have any further queries.
&nbsp;

&nbsp;
Thanks and Regards,
Touseef
Team PluginHive

Hi,&nbsp; 





Have added additional permissions for your users. You should now be able to access order notifications.&nbsp; 





I understand that order completion emails are sent by bigcommerce natively but while the app adds the tracking no. can you not also push the carrier name at the same time? 

Or please suggest if there is a work around. 





Thank you for the screenshot confirmation.&nbsp; 

Yes, the system does automatically pull the order notes, but how can we override that as there is 25 char limit so it misses the information as the customers generally loosely type the note when placing the order.&nbsp; 





And how can we set a default order note like “Leave in Safe place if no answer” which is generally used by carrier so that they don’t take the parcel back.&nbsp; 





Appreciate your help &amp; input to solve this. Thank you.&nbsp; 













Regards, 

Kennedy Wild

Hello Kennedy Wild,
&nbsp;
For the case to show the shipping carrier name along with the tracking number, please allow us some time to check this case further.
&nbsp;
We will update you soon on this.
&nbsp;
For the order notes on the label, the restriction of 25 characters is from the shipping carrier API and not from the app itself. As such, more than 25 characters cannot be printed on the label as of now.
&nbsp;
Additionally, feature for providing a default delivery instruction when order note is not currently not available with the app. I am forwarding your request to our team to check its feasibility.
&nbsp;
We will get back to you with an update soon.
&nbsp;
Thanks and Regards,
Touseef
Team PluginHive

L3: https://pluginhive.slack.com/archives/C02E15X8X0C/p1772629015324009
&nbsp;
UK Customer using BSS-MCSL with ParcelForce has shared a case and requirement.
&nbsp;
Case -
Customer wants to show the carrier name along with the tracking number in the Order Completion emails to customer.
Currently, only the tracking number is being used in the email as it seems like only tracking number is being updated by the app in BigCommerce Order.
Need help from team to check and confirm if the carrier name is also being passed by the app to BigCommerce for the order.
&nbsp;
Attached screenshots of BigCommerce Order 93702 which is fulfilled from the app and also of the fulfillment summary RequestResponse where the shipping provider is passed as empty as ---- "shipping_provider":"" -----
Also attached the Order Fulfillment RequestResponse XML for reference.
&nbsp;
Could you please check the case and confirm if the carrier name/details are passed to BigCommerce Order along with the tracking number when the order is fulfilled from the app?
&nbsp;
Requirement -&nbsp;
Customer has a requirement to show a default delivery instruction (like “Leave in Safe place if no answer”) on the ParcelForce label when the order note is not available.&nbsp;
When order note is available, it should be printed on the label. This is currently working as expected and first 25 characters of Order Note is printed on the label.
Could you please let us know if option to add a default delivery instruction on the label can be made available from the app?
&nbsp;
URL - https://store-17gicadb8v.mybigcommerce.com
Account Id - 08a82e5b-70df-4e1d-8fd9-6d583b11fac2
&nbsp;
BigCommerce Access -&nbsp;
URL - https://login.bigcommerce.com/login
Store - Kennedy Wild Bird Food &amp; Pet Supplies
Username: support@pluginhive.com
Password: #7!-b##k/jm6qS3

Hi Kennedy,
&nbsp;
Thank you for your patience.
&nbsp;
We have identified the reason why the carrier name is not being passed along with the tracking details for ParcelForce. Our team is aware of this and it will be resolved in an upcoming release.
&nbsp;
Regarding the delivery instructions, any note entered in the Order Note will be printed on the label (up to the first 25 characters). Currently, there isn’t an option to add a default delivery and this cannot be configured from the app.
&nbsp;
Please let us know if you have any questions. We’ll be happy to help.
&nbsp;
Best regards,
Priyanka
Team PluginHive
